5:
Um... Could I have your attention for
a moment?
8:
As much as it pains me to admit,
Ryouki was right. I am an artist.
10:
But I won't be able to devote myself
with the same passion and love as
she does, even if I want to keep
going.
13:
Not so long as I keep running away
from this power. Would you help me
learn how to master it?
18:
Do you even need to ask? Of course
we will!
22:
Yeah, we'll do whatever we can to
help.
29:
That being said, we can't afford to
be reckless. We don't want another
rampaging drawing on our hands.
30:
Suizen told us the key to gaining
control lies in your memories...
Perhaps we can start there?
34:
The dragonâ€”it's a manifestation of
my fears.
37:
The more scared I am, the more it
destroys. If we don't purify the
shikigami at the heart of this, I'll just
keep hurting others with my art.
41:
Sounds to me like the solution's
simple!
44:
We beat the big bad dragon up and
show it who's boss!
54: But I doubt the battle will be easy.
58:
The dragon's power is immense. We
were only able to defeat it the first
time with Suizen and Mizuchi's aid.
60:
There's also the problem of the
exorcism. Simply defeating it won't
solve the issue.
64:
I need to make it acknowledge me
as its master.
66:
Considering my track record, this
idea doesn't exactly inspire
confidence, but...
70:
This is... the painting from the other
day!
74:
Suizen asked me to deliver it. He
said, "You must first banish your
fears if you are to purify a monster."
78:
I will succeed, no matter what.
Please, lend me your aid.
82:
You can wait somewhere safe, if you
want. I don't blame you for being
scared.
86:
Nuh-uh. We're gonna conquer our
fears together. I'm already behind,
and I won't let you pull ahead any
further.
88:
Not that... I'm any help in battle... I'm
only going to get in the way, aren't I?
94:
Thank you, Ryouki. I'd probably still
be hiding in my room if you hadn't
dragged me out.
96: I owe all my progress to you.
100:
H-hold on, you can't say that kinda
stuff right now!
102:
Remember what Inaho said about
foreshadowing?
105:
Ah, that... death flag or something
that appears in stories, right?
108: Y-yeah! Don't say stuff that'll jinx us!
112:
All right, I'll save the rest for after
we're finished.
117:
I won't let you hold me back any
longer.
118:
Rise from your slumber... Release
your rage, dragon!
122:
I... am thou... A reflection... of your
heart...
128:
Steel yourself! Something else is
different about it too!
134: It's all right. I understand now.
136:
My younger self created it as a way
to shield herself from the world, out
of fear and desperation... But
because of that, it only knows
destruction.
138:
Tremble before me... Kneel... For all
will be reduced to nothing...
141:
Thank you. You protected me, just
like you were supposed to.
144:
But I'm not that girl anymore. I no
longer need your strength. I have
found friends who will stand by my
side.
150:
Enough. I'm not scared anymore. I
can see the world for all its beauty.
152:
...But most of all, I have found a
reason to paint.
154: A fellow artist who looks up to me...
157:
Whose love for art will be the
strength that carries me forward!
160:
Fool! Unacceptable... You will FALL TO
ME!
163:
I'm sorry, but this is how it must be!
Come!
